OL,3,CHospice boss makes 'devastating'
OL,4,Cdecision to cut back end-of-life
OL,5,Cservices
OL,7,FRight up to the age of 96, Joan was
OL,8,Fvery independent and it was important
OL,9,Fto her that she could be cared for at
OL,10,Fhome.
OL,12,FSarah said: "She (Joan) loved her
OL,13,Flittle bungalow and for us as a family
OL,14,Fto see her in her own nightie, in her
OL,15,Fown bed, under her own duvet, just
OL,16,Fmeant the world to us.
OL,18,F"They would come in and brush gran's
OL,19,Fhair, put hand cream on her hands, all
OL,20,Fthe things that would've been
OL,21,Fimportant to gran.
OL,26,@tD@RpmtD@Wpn
